Date:  0/0/1898
Source:  Austral English
Author:  MORRIS
Vol / Page:  388
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Rifleman</i>, n. a bird of New Zealand, <i>Acanthisitta chloris</i>,

Buller; Maori name, <i>Titipounamu</i>. See quotation. The name is sometimes applied also to the Rifle-bird [? in Australia] (q.v.).
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1898
Source:  Merriam-Webster Third International
Author:
Vol / Page:  2030
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Rii.fle-man</i> (r&imacr.i.f'l-man), <i>n. [Add.] </i>2. (Zoo.].) A small passerine bird of New Zealand (<i>Acanthidositta chloris</i>); so called from its green and bronze plumange, which is thought to resemble the uniform of the early British volunteer rifle corps. <i>Buller</i>.
